<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1688,2039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
We do not name this mature, but probably not fully terminal, male. It was collected in the vicinity of the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1797,1823]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just &amp; Wilson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Menzies" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[272,509,1832,1858]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Cryosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrons">
<emphasis box="[272,509,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Cryosignum latifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above), only a few month later. There is thus a possibility that the specimen could be the so far unknown male of that species, although it differs from the female in the shape of the lateral margins of pereionites 2–4. While that could be an expression of sexual dimorphism, the issue cannot be resolved until the sexes are collected together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1688,2039]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="417" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
We refer the specimen to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Just &amp; Wilson" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[484,621,1976,2002]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Cryosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,621,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Cryosignum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of presence of a mandible palp (observed but not illustrated), an oval pereiopod I carpus, 2 robust setae on pereiopod I propodus, smooth pleotelson margins, and a straight, api- cally truncate uropodal endopod. This combination of characters distinguishes 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Just &amp; Wilson" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1026,1163,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Cryosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1163,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Cryosignum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other genera in the 
<emphasis box="[151,483,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1910" box="[151,305,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Austrosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Austrosignum</taxonomicName>
– 
<taxonomicName authorityName="George &amp; Stromberg" authorityYear="1968" box="[320,483,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Munnogonium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Munnogonium</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
complex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<bibRefCitation author="Menzies, R. J." box="[199,368,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref25721" refString="Menzies, R. J. (1962) The zoogeography, ecology, and systematics of the Chilean marine isopods. Reports of the Lund University Chile Expedition 1948 - 49, Lunds Universitets Arsskrift, Neue Folge, Avd. 2, 57, 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1962">Menzies (1962</bibRefCitation>
, fig.11) illustrated this specimen with the caption (part) “…A, 
<typeStatus box="[1059,1157,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">holotype</typeStatus>
male in toto.” That statement was clearly an unintended error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,295,321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Remarks</emphasis>
. In their study of the isopod fauna of the South Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[968,1164,295,321]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Tristan da Cunha</collectingCountry>
Archipelago 
<bibRefCitation author="Sievertsen, E. &amp; Holthuis, L. B." pageId="16" pageNumber="417" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref26251" refString="Sievertsen, E. &amp; Holthuis, L. B. (1980) The marine isopod Crustacea of the Tristan da Cunha Archipelago. Gunneria, 35, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1980">Sievertsen and Holthuis (1980)</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of a single male of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Richardson, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[840,1314,331,358]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Paramunna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis box="[840,1092,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Paramunna antarctica</emphasis>
(Richardson, 1906)
</taxonomicName>
from Stoltenhoff island, (
<geoCoordinate box="[332,426,366,393]" degrees="37" direction="south" minutes="25" orientation="latitude" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" precision="925" value="-37.416668">37°25’S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[440,542,367,393]" degrees="12" direction="west" minutes="30" orientation="longitude" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" precision="925" value="-12.5">12°30’W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[556,660,366,393]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" unit="m" value="37.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="30.0">30–45 m</quantity>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Just, J. &amp; Wilson, G. D." box="[681,920,367,393]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" pagination="377 - 466" refId="ref25291" refString="Just, J. &amp; Wilson, G. D. F (2004) Revision of the Paramunna complex (Isopoda: Asellota: Paramunnidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 18, 377 - 466. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 03027" type="journal article" year="2004">Just &amp; Wilson (2004</bibRefCitation>
, table 1) revived Richardson’s original genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1906" box="[151,296,403,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Austrimunna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Austrimunna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Richardson, 1906" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1906" box="[467,936,403,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Austrimunna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis box="[467,731,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Austrimunna antarctica</emphasis>
Richardson, 1906
</taxonomicName>
. However, Richardson’s species is part of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G O Sars" authorityYear="1866" box="[151,283,439,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Paramunna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,283,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Paramunna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Just, J. &amp; Wilson, G. D." box="[404,632,439,465]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" pagination="377 - 466" refId="ref25291" refString="Just, J. &amp; Wilson, G. D. F (2004) Revision of the Paramunna complex (Isopoda: Asellota: Paramunnidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 18, 377 - 466. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 03027" type="journal article" year="2004">Just &amp; Wilson 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and not he 
<emphasis box="[774,1101,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1910" box="[774,929,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Austrosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Austrosignum</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName authorityName="George &amp; Stromberg" authorityYear="1968" box="[938,1101,439,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Munnogonium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Munnogonium</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
complex under consideration here. The specimen shown by Sievertsen &amp; Holthuis (fig. 27) is a species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Just &amp; Wilson" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1030,1167,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Cryosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1167,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Cryosignum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Just &amp; Wilson" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1299,1436,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Cryosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Cryosignum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. of this paper, but because of lack of detailed description by Sievertsen and Holthuis and differences in rendition between Sievertsen and Holthuis’ and our illustrations we cannot be certain they belong to the same species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
